The university's Centre for Innovative Education and Communication Technology was torched on Tuesday. CAPE TOWN Police are investigating a case of arson and theft after a building was targeted at the University of the Western Cape (UWC).The Centre for Innovative Education and Communication Technology was torched on Tuesday. More than a dozen computers were also stolen.Meanwhile, police are also probing a petrol bomb attack at the Cape Peninsula University of Technology s Cape Town campus earlier this week.